snippet.textDisplay: Listen to Hislop and Moreno, LOL.  After ManU has won the match, they forget how directionless the team was in the middle 60% of the first half. The threat of a score was always there; ManC weren't the most fluid in the box and I would even say they were for the most part not very commanding as they approached the box but that's quite different from saying they were looking like they weren't going to score. snippet.textDisplay: As a neutral, I just enjoyed the performance of united in this match. The effort from the players was fantastic. they were running a lot, closing down and took the game to City in the first half. For once, united fans should believe in Ole and the process he is talking about. All his signings were in the match and made the difference. AWB ensured that Sterling didn't get a free run, all this talk about city missing KDb is ridiculous, wasn't the pundits saying city have a bench as good as their first team, so where does this come from?? United is improving and Ole deserves credit for it. Just like Arteta deserves credit for Arsenal's improvement. In the last 5 games, only Liverpool(12) have taken more points than United(11) and Arsenal (11).
